</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phoenix24601>Phoenix24601</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#3333ff>(6/19/03 11:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Blind Watchmaker and junkyard 747's</span><hr size=1> DL, that'd be why I said I don't know if I agree with it.  I've looked over both articles and have found both of them to make some good points, while leaving their argument wanting in other areas.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=doublelatte>Double Latte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Got Milk?</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#3333ff>(6/20/03 7:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Blind Watchmaker and junkyard 747's</span><hr size=1> In what ways did you find the Dawkins essay &quot;wanting&quot;? Please explain.<br>
