</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phoenix24601>Phoenix24601</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#3333ff>(6/20/03 1:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Blind Watchmaker and junkyard 747's</span><hr size=1> He discussed well the workings of evolution, but when it came time to his discussion of the origins of the universe he was quite elusive.  He quickly mentioned another person's book, and quickly stated a one line conclusion, but he did not do anything to back it up.  The least he could have done is to quote something from the book to emphasize that point.  I do understand why he wouldn't want to go too much into detail about soemthing that is outside his realm of expertise, but if he was not going to include more about that section, then he sould not have covered it at all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=218.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=218.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.emailToFriend?topicID=218.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image